                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/275</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Blocker</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Eagle Pass</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-12T17:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 12, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s September 11, 1916, 4 p.m. in answer to my June 20, 1916, 10 a.m.
                    Confiscation order was revoked when it was seen by State officials of Coahuila
                    that intervention would not occur as was believed when order was given on June
                    19.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blocker</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
